Anonymous Fri 07 May 2021 12:22:37 No.38494604 Report
Quoted By: >>38494761
https://desuarchive.org/trash/thread/38477556/#q38493515
>I was wondering if i should rewrite my old stories or just keep making new ones?
>I kind of want to have an enjoyable experience for my reader... but i kind of want to finish what i'm working on so i can continue working on my larger project.

I would say I've thought of this too but don't be too worried about hating your old work. It's all on the road to progress. If you want to get better at writing you do need feedback but rewriting the same work over and over again can burnout and will turn readers (and beta readers) off.

Or you can have your improving writing implemented.

One of my older non-hmofa stories (which I published on fanfic.net) was written from a first person POV and the writing changed over time to reflect how the protagonist wrote in his journal, showing how he matures as a person and gets better at his craft. It's one of my longer running pieces. I look back at the earlier chapters and cringe but I don't want to change it.
